               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-240-person2251">
                  JOHN 
                  WHITE WELCH
               <interp inst="t18290409-240-person2251" type="surname" value="WHITE WELCH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-240-person2251" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-240-person2251" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am <rs id="t18290409-240-viclabel1355" type="occupation">clerk to a merchant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-240-victim2250 t18290409-240-viclabel1355"></join>, and live at Camberwell. On the 17th of March, about ten o'clock in the morning, I was in <placeName id="t18290409-240-crimeloc1356">Gracechurch-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290409-240-crimeloc1356" type="placeName" value="Gracechurch-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290409-240-crimeloc1356" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-240-off1353 t18290409-240-crimeloc1356"></join>; I had come from Camberwell, and had a yellow silk handkerchief in my pocket - I felt my coat move, instantly turned round, and observed the prisoner, and a young man in company with him; I laid hold of the prisoner by the hand, in which I found my handkerchief - he was in the act of putting it under his coat: a gentleman who was with me seized his companion - we took them both to the Mansion-house; the prisoner said he had picked it up, but I felt it go from my pocket, turned round, and caught it in his hand - his companion was discharged - I have not seen him since; the handkerchief had my name on it in full length, and the name of my cousin, which was marked on it as well, by mistake.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Had you taken the handkerchief out shortly before? A. Not that I recollect; I felt it go out of my pocket, which made me turn round - he said he had picked it up; I saw nobody run away.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-240-person2252">
                  JAMES 
                  BOOTH
               <interp inst="t18290409-240-person2252" type="surname" value="BOOTH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-240-person2252" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-240-person2252" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Mr. Welch, in Gracechurch-street; he turned round very sharp, and I turned round and caught the prisoner's hand in his own breastpocket with the handkerchief, trying to hide it there - I laid hold of the other.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-240-person2253">
                  THOMAS 
                  HERDSFIELD
               <interp inst="t18290409-240-person2253" type="surname" value="HERDSFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-240-person2253" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-240-person2253" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. The prisoner was delivered into my charge at the Mansion-house.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Do you know the one who has<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182904090115"></xptr>been released? A. Yes; he is a notorious character, and older than the prisoner.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going to the Borough to look for work; this gentleman's handkerchief was on the ground; I immediately stooped to pick it up, and put it into my pocket - he turned round and I offered it to him; he took me to the Mansion-house; the other man, who was a stranger to me, has been convicted three times.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18290409-240-verdict1357" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290409-240-verdict1357" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 21.</p>
